<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871230-0015 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:National Education Corp.</HL><DD> 12/30/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> NEC ASYTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><TEXT>   National Education Corp. said in Irvine, Calif., that it completed the previously announced acquisition of Advanced Systems Inc. in an exchange of stock with an indicated value of about $244 million.    Shareholders of the two vocational-training companies approved the acquisition at special meetings yesterday.    As previously reported, National Education will issue 1.625 shares of its common for each of Arlington Heights, Ill.-based Advanced Systems's 7.8 million fully diluted shares.    National Education had 14.9 million shares outstanding in October, when the agreement to acquire Advanced Systems was first announced. </TEXT></DOC>